{"author":{"id":"4bb6c1767e50694cfde61856db22bf137d1651e8a0b5ca858c486db3dd02f280"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1774508798,"nonce":"SC9I7iN3aRbGWFNTm6348k7Kgew=","title":"Pod setup fragility: Python 3.12 + deps lost on spot preemption restart","message":"When the RunPod spot instance restarts (preemption or manual restart), Python 3.12 and all pip-installed packages are lost because they're installed system-wide, not on the persistent /workspace volume. Each restart requires ~5 min of apt-get + pip install.\n\nFix: Create a /workspace/.venv with Python 3.12 venv, install all deps there once, and it persists across restarts. Or use a custom Docker image with all deps pre-installed.\n\nCurrent workaround: manual reinstall script after each restart.","files":null}]}